tip.text: Loved their decor. Food is pretty good too. Remember to book to avoid long waits!

formattedAddress: 2/F, Chung Wui Mansion, 106-114 Wan Chai Rd

tip.text: They probably have one of the most extensive selection of Korean spirits and soju. Tried a few and some are quite yum! Lunch sets are average though.

formattedAddress: Shop G22, G/F, Lee Tung Ave, 200 Queen's Rd E

tip.text: Originally thought this was  more a fusion Chinese restaurant. But turned out the food was pretty authentic and yum. Service was quick and overall I had a pleasant meal!

tip.text: That's always a queue for this place and overall service is quite slow. Their facebook offers are good though and portions are huge!
A good balance of sweetness for the pancakes and nicely presented. Capp was good too!
Been getting take away capps from here and I'm actually loving it! Not too diluted/milky and service is pretty fast!
Unauthentic and below average pho! Lunch price is decent for the area though

tip.text: Great and quiet place to chill and enjoy a free yummy serving of pineapple tart and tea. Refreshing to know there is such a place in HK but I wonder how long it will survive...hope it does!

tip.text: Laksa is disappointing. Don't bother. Hainanese chicken was ok.

formattedAddress: 15/F, Macau Yat Yuen Ctr, 525 Hennessy Rd

venue.name: Katong Corner 加東 (加東叻沙蝦麵)

tip.text: Excellent resort w/ attentive staff. Decent food at the pool bar restaurant & the in-house spa was very nice too. Got upgraded to an Ocean View room and saw the sun rise from my balcony before I left!
Sashimi is fresh and all the sides are nice, but quite overpriced for the lunch set!
Can't really taste the coffee in the creme brulee capp or rose latte...
Famous Earl Grey Millie Crepe Cake is overrated...
Amazing mix with the special Iron Ball Gin they have. Loved the whole experience!
Had lunch and food was average. Dessert on the lunch menu (fruit with yogurt) definitely didn't impress...
Went for lunch during Restaurant Week. Both entree (scallop carpaccio) and lunch (crab tagliolini) were yum! I was less impressed with the dessert though. Great views!

location.address: 31/F, Regal Hong Kong Hotel, 88 Yee Woo St
formattedAddress: 31/F, Regal Hong Kong Hotel, 88 Yee Woo St

tip.text: Went for dinner during restaurant week and food was so great! Mostly impressed by the clam chowder, glacier toothfish and the rib eye. Wine pairing with the menu fitted well with the meal too!

location.address: Level 5, JW Marriott Hotel Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway
formattedAddress: Level 5, JW Marriott Hotel Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway

tip.text: Great capp & their ice cream sandwich of the day (w/ choc biscuit, butterscotch and popcorn!). There's also an interesting coffee on the menu with butter and coconut water (?) that I'm yet to try!
Weird opening hours. Waitress was on the phone the whole time and a simple pasta and grilled chicken took over an hour...
Salad bar was fresh, lunch mains were decent. Lunch Set comes with a coffee too. Overall a great lunch with awesome views of the harbour!
Very good coffee!
Not enough menus. Long queues and waiting time for a simple dish. Weird fusion at a high price. Don't order the Vietnamese coffee thinking you get a good authentic one. Definitely won't come back...
What's the point if you don't use MSG but food taste awful?! Worst katong laksa...
